steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"4be6d","text":"Store alpha-Synuclein fibril preparations at   with appropriate biohazard precautions and labels until use.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":45,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"e0hma","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"temperature","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"error_temperature":false,"guid":"","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"temperature":"-80","unit":10}}}}

steps.section: PFF preparation (to be done on the same day as experiment)
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"47kds","text":"On the day of usage, briefly thaw fibrils on ice.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: PFF preparation (to be done on the same day as experiment)
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"da6lu","text":"Transfer required quantity of fibrils to the appropriate tube compatible with your sonicator. Dilute fibrils with normal saline (0.9% NaCl) if required. We used fibrils at a concentration of 5mg/mL.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: PFF preparation (to be done on the same day as experiment)
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"56fs8","text":"Program Covaris S220 water bath sonicator to: ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2jetc","text":"18 W peak incident power;","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8s7cf","text":"20% duty factor;","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"edkqu","text":"50 cycles per burst;","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ntrg","text":"150 s.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"l331","text":"Anesthetize mouse with isoflurane in an enclosed chamber.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1tuhs","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4i0f8","text":"Using a 2µl Hamilton Company syringe, take up 1µl of sonicated PFFs or normal saline (0.9% NaCl) using a micro-syringe computerized pump.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cubku","text":"Program the micro-syringe computerized pump to deliver 1 μL mouse PFFs (5 mg/mL) or sterile saline (0.9% NaCl) at a rate of 0.1 μL/min (min). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6dmap","text":"Wait 6 months for phenotype development, or however long your experiment requires.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"em4kr","text":"Perform behavioural experiments then collect tissues for biochemical and histological analysis.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ahpg1","text":"Once deeply anesthetized, transfer the mouse to the stereotaxic frame. Insert mouse nose into isoflurane mask.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"flo7q","text":"Align needle to coordinates relative to bregma: −2 mm medial-lateral; +0.2mm antero-posterior.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2osjq","text":"Begin the administration sequence, following the micro-syringe computerized pump's instructions.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fnt84","text":"Leave the needle in place for at least 3 min before its slow withdrawal. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fgrpj","text":"Incise skin. Mark site on skull with a marking pen, and drill 1mm diameter burr hole with handheld drill.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"q4l4","text":"Slowly position the needle to coordinates relative to bregma: −2 mm medial-lateral; +0.2mm antero-posterior and −2.6 mm dorso-ventral (right dorsal striatum).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
